<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 04 at 1:04AM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Val Verde
County through 145 AM CDT...
At 102 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles northwest of Juno, moving southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Juno, Langtry, Pumpville, Pandale, Bakers Crossing and Devils River
State Nat Area Del Norte, and State Highway 163.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
